    mc("'Validity' in research refers to:","The consistency of results across repeated trials","Whether the study actually measures what it claims to measure","The size of the sample","The speed of data collection",1,"Validity: does the instrument/study measure what it intends to measure? Internal validity: are the results due to the variable of interest? External validity: can results generalize?"),
    mc("'Reliability' in research refers to:","The accuracy of the conclusion","The consistency of measurements — the same method applied repeatedly produces similar results","Whether the research question is important","The quality of the sources",1,"Reliability: consistency of measurement. A reliable instrument gives similar results under similar conditions. Can be reliable without being valid (consistent but measuring wrong thing)."),
    mc("IRB (Institutional Review Board) review is required when:","Conducting library research only","Research involves human participants — to ensure ethical treatment, informed consent, and protection from harm","Analyzing published data only","Doing a literature review",1,"IRB: required for human subjects research. Ensures: informed consent, voluntary participation, confidentiality, minimized harm. Even AP Research projects involving surveys may require school IRB approval."),
